<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFB18502FEECFE88FE59FE0C" box="[322,406,374,400]" name="Bolivia" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8628475BFFB18502FF13FE64FC91FE60" blockId="22.[136,1452,373,508]" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB18502FF13FE64FEE9FE28" bold="true" box="[189,294,410,436]" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">Notes:—</emphasis>
This Bolivian endemic may produce up to 
<quantity id="416FEABEFFB18502FCBDFE64FC8FFE28" box="[787,832,410,436]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="233" unit="m" value="2.0">2 m</quantity>
proliferous plants,. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FFB18502FB7CFE65FAF4FE28" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Schlechter" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[1234,1339,410,436]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="22" pageNumber="233" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutex">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB18502FB7CFE65FAF4FE28" box="[1234,1339,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">M. frutex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is also found in 
<collectingCountry id="FE8007CBFFB18502FE8CFE40FEB7FE44" box="[290,376,446,472]" name="Bolivia" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. However, it is distinguished from the latter by its whitish flowers and acute lateral lip lobes 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FFB18502FA23FE41FA6BFE44" box="[1421,1444,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="233">vs</emphasis>
. yellowish to brownish flowers and lip margins obscurely angled.
</paragraph>
